checkMarkets

public static Output checkMarkets(Variables var)
                           throws java.io.IOException,
                                  java.lang.NullPointerException
Gets the value and volume data from the requested markets (by calling dataParser() ), then determines how many distribution startDaysAgo there have been in the last 4 weeks. A distribution day is defined as a day when value decreased and volume increased, with the threshold set at less than 4. Boolean is saved in the marketStatus HashMap.

Parameters:
var -
Returns:
true if less than 4 d-startDaysAgo, false otherwise
Throws:
java.io.IOException
java.lang.NullPointerException
